{
  "text": "for the traffic density \u03c1. Assume that the speed V is not the same for all drivers. More precisely, different drivers differ in their maximal speed w, so that V = w \u03c8(\u03c1), with w \u2208 [w,\u0175] ,w > 0, being transported along the road at the mean traffic speed V . We identify the different behaviors of the different drivers by means of their maximal speed, see also [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . One is thus lead to study the equations \u2202 t \u03c1 + \u2202 x (\u03c1v) = 0 \u2202 t w + v \u2202 x w = 0 with v = w \u03c8(\u03c1) .",
